headline: CVS unit ordered to pay $95 million in Medicare whistleblower lawsuit
summary: CVS Health's pharmacy benefit manager unit must pay the U.S. government $95 million after a federal judge found it overcharged Medicare for prescription drugs. Chief Judge Mitchell Goldberg in Philadelphia ordered the payment by CVS Caremark on Wednesday, following an eight-day non-jury trial in March in the whistleblower case. Goldberg will decide after further briefing whether to triple the award to $285 million under the federal False Claims Act.

headline: CVS Health opens new Workforce Innovation and Talent Center in Chicago
summary: CVS Health® (NYSE: CVS) announced today the opening of its new Workforce Innovation and Talent Center (WITC) in Chicago. The center, situated at the Chicago Baptist Institute, will improve the community's access to workforce training services and provide every participant who completes the program an opportunity to apply for a position at CVS Health.
